The convention in the UK was that it's "disc" for everything except for magnetic storage, which was "disk". With the departure of floppy disks, and the switch to "hard drive", it's mainly "disc" again.
We did the same thing with "programme", which was the spelling for everything except computer programs. But now it's all software and apps, so I don't see "program" much in BrE these days.

